<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=105128557515104></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105128557515104><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=105128557515104>RE: Melee Skills</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=105128557515104#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=202298><span id= >Dashie</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 25th 12:24 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I see you are a &quot;roll&quot; player and not a &quot;role&quot; player as you say. If you are concerned only about living and dying and not establishing a little &quot;identity&quot; for your character, I agree with your response. Sadly this is what these games have become for the most part.<br><br>On the other hand... If you want to increase your defense (which improves your AC) and establish a bit of &quot;battle cleric&quot; into your role, I say melee responsibly. Your first priority is to the safety of the group, unless there is a second cleric as primary healer.<br><br>I was given a crafted velium brawl stick at 15th level. It fits my &quot;role&quot; perfectly. If there is a single mob and we are not taking damage very fast, I step in and beat on it for a bit. When a heal is needed, a buff drops, or we get an add I back off and deal with it. The people I group with know what I am doing and are cool with it. Is kind of funny to see a cleric in there dealing out 60 - 91 (highest) dmg to a mob. I have even been the MT in situations (duoing with a shammy).<br><br>The conditions I use for this are:<br><br>1) at least 80% mana (with KEI)<br>2) single or occasional double mob's<br>3) low chance of wandering adds<br>4) everyone has been buffed and has 80+% HP<br>5) last and MOST important.... I am the MAIN HEALER and that is my first responsibility.<br><br>Quex 52nd Vicar<br>Proud &quot;Battle Cleric&quot;<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
